cs.NI, cs.IT, cs.AI, cs.LG, cs.SY

This paper discusses the challenges and opportunities of using the fast uplink grant for enabling massive machine type communications (MTCs) in cellular networks. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture). The paper also proposes solutions based on machine learning methods, which suggests a possible fit with cs.IT (Information Theory) and cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence). Additionally, the paper discusses traffic prediction, which could be relevant to cs.LG (Machine Learning) and cs.SY (Systems and Control).
